<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04765</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT SETTING MINIMUM STANDARDS FOR THE OPERATION OF INTERNET CAFES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates all Local Government Units to enforce the provisions of this Act and all similar establishments
shall be covered under this Act.

Specifies adequate facilities for establishments offering computer services such as:
a) system, program, or application which can aid the monitoring of the time spent by each client;
b) sufficient ventilation, or if needed, an airconditioning;
c) regularly cleaned comfort room/lavatory with a closed-flush toilet.

Requires other regulations such as: a) a computer may be rented for only six (6) hours per person in
one session; b) students in basic/secondary education shall not be allowed to rent a computer to play
games from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. during weekdays, excluding holidays/other special observances
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>DELOS SANTOS, ALFRED C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-09-23</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2020-01-06)</td><td>2. Salceda (000 2019-12-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2019-09-25</td></tr></table>